{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Appearances","anchor":"Appearances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"brand"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A brand primary color alternative to the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A button with ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","level":2},{"code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\", appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance and button taking full width","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong, isFullWidth: true) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSButton(LocalizedStringKey(\"validate_button\"), bundle: Bundle.module, appearance: .strong) { }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSButton(text: \"Button\",","               icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","               flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Styles","anchor":"Styles"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pressed"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"hovered","type":"text"}]},{"text":" or normal (i.e. ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"enabled","type":"text"}]},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rounded layout","anchor":"Rounded-layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedButtons"},{"type":"text","text":" values of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"WireframeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Colored-surface","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Colored surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface.","type":"text"}]}]},{"anchor":"Specific-behavior","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Specific behavior"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-button","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering"},{"anchor":"Orange","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Orange"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_OrangeCompact"}]},{"anchor":"Sosh","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Sosh"}]},{"anchor":"Wireframe","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Wireframe"}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3.2.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Version"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.10.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Since"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Button is a UI element that triggers an action or event, and is use